# Nginx and UWSGI Configuration on Linux Environment

1) Make two directories in the following path
    /etc/nginx/sites-enabled
    /etc/nginx/sites-available

2) In the sites available directory, make a file 'my-djangoproject.com.conf'
    vim /etc/nginx/sites-available/my-djangoproject.com.conf

    # Write into the file
    server {
        listen 80;

        location / {
                proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000/; # 80 port pr listen kr k 8000 port pr request transfer krdega.
                proxy_redirect off;
                proxy_buffering off;

                proxy_http_version 1.1;
                proxy_set_header Connection "Keep-Alive";
                proxy_set_header Proxy-Connection "Keep-Alive";
        }
    }

3) Now link up two directories 'sites-enabled' and 'sites-available'
    sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/my-djangoproject.com.conf /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/my-djangoproject.com.conf

    # It means whatever you change in sites-available directory it will be automatically
      change in sites-enabled directory.

4) Now run your service using..
    sudo service django-server.service start

    # You can stop the service using 'sudo service django-server.service stop'
    # You can check the status of the service using 'sudo service django-server.service status'


